\pard\f0\fs28  Sect. PHOENIXOPUS (Cass.) Bentham. Inflorescence a pyramidal or spike-like panicle with capitula solitary or in fascicles. Capitula with 4-8 florets. Achenes with 5-11 ribs, gradually contracted into a concolorous beak not longer than body.
