\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. L. acanthifolia} (Willd.) Boiss., {\i Fl. Or.}{\b  3}: 818 (1875) ({\i L. amorgina} Heldr. & Orph. ex Halácsy). Perennial. Rhizome large, covered with remains of leaves. Stem 30-100 cm, erect, striate, glabrous except for the arachnoid-lanate base. Lower leaves very variable in shape, oblong-ovate or spathulate in outline, lobed or pinnatifid, rarely entire, petiolate; upper pinnatipartite, auriculate; all densely arachnoid-lanate on the proximal side of petiole and sometimes on midrib, otherwise glabrous or subglabrous. Capitula subsessile in a spike-like panicle, solitary or in small fascicles. Involucral bracts lanate at apex. Ligules yellow. Achenes 8-9 mm; body oblong-lanceolate, 5- to 7-ribbed, yellowish-brown; beak ½ as long as to as long as body. 2n = 18.{\i  Shady rocks. S. Aegean region.} Cr Gr.
\par 

