\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 3. L. longidentata} Moris ex DC.,{\i  Prodr.}{\b  7}: 139 (1838). Glaucous biennial. Stem up to 100 cm, erect, striate. Lower leaves obovate to lanceolate, laciniate-runcinate to pinnatipartite, narrowed into a petiole, with the undivided part of the lamina 2-8 cm wide; upper ovate in outline, deeply laciniate, dentate, acuminate, with decurrent-amplexicaul base. Inflorescence a pyramidal panicle with ascending branches. Capitula with 5-6(-8) florets. Ligules yellow. Achenes 7-9 mm; body oblong, 7- to 11-ribbed, black; beak 1/3 as long as body.{\i  Calcareous rocks. • Sardegna.} Sa.
